#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:17
msgid ""
"The *active* element can be an Object, vertex, edge or a face. The active"
" element is the last one to be selected and will be shown in a lighter "
"orange color when in *Object mode* and white when in *Edit mode*. With "
"*Active element as Pivot* set to active, all transformations will occur "
"relative to the active element."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:23
msgid ""
"Read more about selecting different :doc:`Pivot Points "
"</editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/index>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:30
msgid ""
"Display of active elements in Object mode is shown on the left of the "
"image where the active element (cube) is a lighter orange. Active "
"elements for vertices, edges and faces in Edit mode are displayed in "
"white and are shown on the right."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:36
msgid "In Object mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:38
msgid ""
"When in *Object mode*, rotation and scaling happen around the active "
"Object's center. This is shown by the figure to the below where the "
"active Object (the cube) remains in the same location (note its position "
"relative to the 3D cursor) while the other Objects rotate and scale in "
"relation to the active element."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:48
msgid "Rotation and scaling with the cube as the active element."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:52
msgid "In Edit mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:54
msgid ""
"Using the active element as a pivot point in *Edit mode* may seem complex"
" but all the possible transformations follow a few rules:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:58
msgid "The pivot point is always at the median of the active element(s)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:59
msgid ""
"The transformations occur by transformation of the **vertices** of the "
"selected element(s). If an unselected element shares one or more vertices"
" with a selected element then the unselected one will get some degree of "
"transformation also."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:63
msgid ""
"Let's examine the following examples: in each case we will see that the "
"two rules apply."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:67
msgid "Single selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:69
msgid ""
"When one single element is selected it becomes automatically active. In "
"the image below, you can see that when it is transformed its vertices "
"move, with the consequence that any adjacent element which shares one or "
"more vertices with the active element is also transformed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:78
msgid "Edit mode and only one element selected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:81
msgid "Let's review each case:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:83
msgid ""
"*Faces* have their pivot point where their selection dot appears, which "
"is where the median of their vertices is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:84
msgid ""
"*Edges* have their pivot point on their middle since this is always where"
" the median of an edge is."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:85
msgid ""
"A single *Vertex* has no dimensions at all so it can't show any "
"transformation (except translation, which is not affected by the pivot "
"point)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:90
msgid "Multiple selection"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:92
msgid ""
"When multiple elements are selected they all transform. The pivot points "
"stay in the same place as what we've seen above, with only one exception "
"for Fgons. In the image below, the selected elements have been rotated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:101
msgid "Edit mode and multiple selections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:104
msgid ""
"For *Faces* the transformation occurs around the selection dot of the "
"active face."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:105
msgid ""
"*Edges* also keep the same behavior with their pivot point at their "
"median."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:106
msgid "*Fgons* behave exactly like faces."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/active_element.rst:107
msgid ""
"There is a case for *Vertices* this time: the active Vertex is where the "
"pivot point resides. All other vertices are transformed relative to it."
msgstr ""

